            <h2 class="right-heading">7 Allergy-Relief Plants to Make Springtime Easier for You!</h2>
            <!-- Introductory paragraphs -->
            <p>Spring is upon us, and summer is fast approaching! While many would agree that warmer temperatures are more pleasant, some dread the days when the cold begins to thaw.</p>
            <p>The warmer the temperatures, the higher the chances of allergies - we're talking nightmarish flare-ups for those who suffer from seasonal allergies. Irritation, sneezing, coughing, and even more respiratory issues - the list is never-ending!</p>

            <!-- Section heading for plant list -->
            <h1 class="right-heading">7 Indoor Plants that Help with Allergies!</h1>

            <!-- Snake Plant section -->
            <h1>1. Snake Plant Golden Hahnii</h1>
            <div class="image-container">
                <!-- Centered image for the plant -->
                <img src="../../public/images/blogs/all1.webp" alt="Snake Plant Golden Hahnii">
            </div>
            <p>No pollen, no allergies! The Golden Hahnii Snake plant is a savior during the summer and springtime.</p>
            <p>It filters out harmful pollutants and toxins, giving you cleaner and healthier indoor air. Overall, this leaves you with a more relaxing environment to breathe free - the most wonderful allergy-relief plants!</p>

            <!-- Peace Lily section -->
            <h1>2. Peace Lily</h1>
            <div class="image-container">
                <!-- Centered image for the plant -->
                <img src="../../public/images/blogs/all2.webp" alt="Peace Lily">
            </div>
            <p>These stunning flowering allergy-relief plants do produce pollen. But their pollen is heavier and does not float around, thus eliminating the risk of allergies.</p>
            <p>The best part? Peace Lilies are NASA-approved air purifiers, which makes them the perfect fit for spaces that need a natural way to combat pollution and pollen.</p>

            <!-- Chinese Evergreen section -->
            <h1>3. Chinese Evergreen/Aglaonema Plants</h1>
            <div class="image-container">
                <!-- Centered image for the plant -->
                <img src="../../public/images/blogs/all3.webp" alt="Chinese Evergreen">
            </div>
            <p>The stunning Aglaonema plant is considered a pretty allergy-friendly plant because it does not cause any respiratory irritation.</p>
            <p>Yes, it is a flowering plant like the Peace Lily. But it won't do you any harm, unlike major pollen producers!</p>

            <!-- Philodendron section -->
            <h1>4. Philodendron Plants</h1>
            <div class="image-container">
                <!-- Centered image for the plant -->
                <img src="../../public/images/blogs/all4.webp" alt="Philodendron Plants">
            </div>
            <p>Philodendron plants are undoubtedly one of the best kinds of plants you can bring home. Jaw-droppingly beautiful and super easy to care for, these top the list of houseplants that help with allergies.</p>
            <p>With the right care and lots of love, these plants can grow to develop large leaves that will absorb even more toxins from the air, thus reducing the effects of summertime pollution on your lungs!</p>

            <!-- Bamboo Palm section -->
            <h1>5. Bamboo Palm</h1>
            <div class="image-container">
                <!-- Centered image for the plant -->
                <img src="../../public/images/blogs/all5.webp" alt="Bamboo Palm">
            </div>
            <p>This beautiful tropical plant is high on the list of every plant lover's list of must-haves. However, we're sure you've probably always wondered if bringing this plant home will do any good for your allergies.</p>
            <p>Well, good news, because it will! Bamboo Palms are stunning tropical plants that do not produce any airborne irritants. So, no allergy flare-ups.</p>

            <!-- Ficus Lyrata section -->
            <h1>6. Ficus Lyrata</h1>
            <div class="image-container">
                <!-- Centered image for the plant -->
                <img src="../../public/images/blogs/all6.webp" alt="Ficus Lyrata">
            </div>
            <p>The Ficus Lyrata does not produce any harmful pollen or respiratory irritants. All it does is clean the air around you and give you a healthier indoor space!</p>
            <p>Basically, it gives you all it can and asks for only a little care in return! The perfect allergy-relief plant for every space!</p>

            <!-- Ponytail Palm section -->
            <h1>7. Ponytail Palm</h1>
            <div class="image-container">
                <!-- Centered image for the plant -->
                <img src="../../public/images/blogs/all7.webp" alt="Ponytail Palm">
            </div>
            <p>We've got another Palm plant that tops this list - the beautiful and unique Ponytail Palm! This super low-maintenance plant is the perfect air purifier that cleanses its environment effortlessly.</p>
            <p>Just like the Bamboo Palm, the Nolina Palm also does not produce any pollen or respiratory irritants. Plus, its ability to absorb harmful air pollutants and produce 10x more oxygen in return makes it one of the best indoor plants that help with allergies!</p>
